1.	The pivot is just the value which separates the bigger list from the smaller list. This number doesnâ€™t have to be
the value at the middle index, it can be any of the values in the list as pivot is relative to the whole data set.

2.	Test cases:

In order to properly test quick_select(), you must test the function with different lists and k values. You must test
it on odd, even, sorted, and unsorted lists. You must check it on random, initial, and final k values.


1,2,3   k = 0  __> 1   test on ordered list
1,3,6,5   k=2 ----> 5   test on random list
1,1,1,1  k=3   ----> 3  test on identical list
1,8,5,2,9,7,5 k = 2 ----> 5 test on k is random
1,2,3,4 k =1 ------> 2  test on even list

4,3,2,1,0 k=3 ----> 3 test on odd list

1,2,3,4 k = 0 ----> 1 initial index
5.7.4.2 k = 3 -----> 7 final index

3.	For quick select (in seconds):

